<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/favicon.png">
    <meta name="description"
        content="Start your own container garden on your balcony or patio. Learn about the best plants for containers, pot types, and essential care tips for small-space gardening.">
    <title>Container Gardening for Small Spaces - Home Hub</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com/3.4.16"></script>
    <script>
        tailwind.config = {
            theme: {
                extend: {
                    colors: {
                        primary: "#14B8A6",
                        secondary: "#0F766E",
                    },
                    borderRadius: {
                        none: "0px",
                        sm: "4px",
                        DEFAULT: "8px",
                        md: "12px",
                        lg: "16px",
                        xl: "20px",
                        "2xl": "24px",
                        "3xl": "32px",
                        full: "9999px",
                        button: "8px",
                    },
                },
            },
        };
    </script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Pacifico&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/remixicon/4.6.0/remixicon.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/responsive.css">
</head>

<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/gardening" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Gardening</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">Container Gardening</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                Container Gardening Ideas for Small Balconies
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/container-gardening.webp"
                                    alt="Beautiful container garden on a small city balcony"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    You don't need a massive backyard to enjoy the rewards of gardening. Container
                                    gardening allows anyone with a balcony, patio, or even just a sunny windowsill to
                                    grow a variety of plants, from colorful flowers to fresh herbs and vegetables.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choosing the Right Containers
                                </h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The container you choose is just as important as the plant
                                    you put in it. Consider drainage and material.</p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Terra Cotta:</strong> Breathable but dries out quickly. Great for
                                        Mediterranean herbs.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Plastic:</strong> Lightweight and retains moisture well. Ideal for leafy
                                        greens.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Ceramic:</strong> Holds water and looks beautiful, but can be heavy and
                                        fragile.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Best Plants for Containers</h2>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Herbs:</strong> Basil, oregano, and mint thrive in small pots.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Vegetables:</strong> Cherry tomatoes and peppers work well in deeper
                                        containers.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Flowers:</strong> Petunias and pansies provide vibrant color all season.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    Container gardening is a flexible and rewarding way to bring nature into your living
                                    space. Start small, learn your plants' needs, and watch your balcony garden
                                    flourish.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
                        <div class="sticky top-8 space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Quick Tip</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-600">Ensure all your containers have drainage holes at the bottom.
                                    Without them, water can pool and cause root rot.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
            <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>